<h2 id="key-features">🔧 Key Features Breakdown</h2>

<h3>Triple Pixel Attribution</h3>

The Triple Pixel is the platform's core differentiator. It combines first-party data collection, server-side tracking, and machine learning models to attribute conversions across channels. Unlike platform pixels that each claim credit for the same sale, Triple Pixel deduplicates conversions and assigns fractional credit based on touchpoint influence.

In our testing, the pixel captured 18-27% more conversions than Meta's native pixel across iOS users. This isn't magic—it's first-party data doing what third-party cookies no longer can. The pixel also feeds data back to ad platforms via CAPI integrations, improving their optimization algorithms with cleaner signals.

One limitation: the pixel requires customers to land on your site to track initial touchpoints. View-through attribution remains dependent on platform data, which limits accuracy for awareness campaigns. For direct response campaigns driving clicks, the accuracy improvement is substantial.

<h3>Unified Dashboard & Summary Page</h3>

The Summary Page consolidates Shopify, Meta, Google, TikTok, Snapchat, Pinterest, and Klaviyo data into a single view. Real-time updates show orders as they happen with channel attribution attached. The MER (Marketing Efficiency Ratio) calculation—total revenue divided by total ad spend—provides a cleaner north star than individual platform ROAS metrics.

Custom date comparisons let you measure against last week, last month, or year-over-year with one click. The cohort analysis tools show how different acquisition channels perform over 30, 60, and 90-day windows—critical for understanding true customer value beyond the initial purchase.

<h3>Creative Cockpit</h3>

Creative Cockpit analyzes ad creative performance across platforms with attributed revenue data. You can see which specific ads, images, and copy drive actual purchases—not just clicks or platform-reported conversions. The hook rate, hold rate, and click-through metrics help identify creative fatigue before ROAS tanks.

This feature alone justified the subscription cost for one apparel brand we work with. They discovered their top-performing Meta creative was actually their worst performer when measured by attributed revenue. The creative drove cheap clicks that rarely converted.

<h3>Moby AI Recommendations</h3>

Moby is Triple Whale's AI assistant, analyzing your data to surface optimization opportunities. It identifies underperforming campaigns, suggests budget reallocations, and flags anomalies. The recommendations are genuinely useful about 60% of the time—not revolutionary, but better than most AI marketing tools we've tested.

The AI excels at pattern recognition across large data sets. For operators managing multiple brands or heavy campaign volumes, Moby catches things human review misses. For smaller operations with simpler setups, the value is marginal.

<h3>Affluencer Hub (Influencer Attribution)</h3>

Affluencer Hub tracks influencer campaign performance using unique discount codes and landing pages. The integration with affiliate platforms like Refersion and Impact adds influencer data to your unified attribution model. For brands spending heavily on influencer marketing, this closes a major attribution gap.

<div class="callout-orange">
<strong>Watch Out:</strong> Affluencer Hub pricing is separate from core Triple Whale plans. Budget an additional $199-499/month depending on influencer volume. The feature is powerful but can double your total Triple Whale costs.
</div>

