<h2 id="implementation-tips">🛠️ Implementation Tips From Our Testing</h2>

After deploying Triple Whale across numerous brands, here's what separates successful implementations from frustrating ones:

**First, install the Triple Pixel on all pages immediately**—not just checkout. Attribution accuracy depends on tracking the full customer journey. We've seen brands install only on thank-you pages and wonder why their data looks incomplete.

**Second, run Triple Whale parallel to your existing tracking for 30 days** before making budget decisions. Compare Triple Whale attribution to your current approach and post-purchase surveys. Build confidence in the data before shifting spend.

**Third, configure Slack alerts thoughtfully.** The real-time order notifications are addictive but overwhelming at scale. We recommend channel-specific alerts for high-value orders only, plus daily summary digests for overall performance.

**Fourth, schedule weekly Creative Cockpit reviews.** The creative insights lose value if reviewed sporadically. Build a systematic process for analyzing ad performance and acting on the data.

**Fifth, leverage the customer journey reports** for email segmentation. The acquisition source data feeds directly into Klaviyo segments, enabling channel-specific post-purchase flows that convert at higher rates.

